# Amni-Code Architecture Map - Grok Computer Use Agent v0.1.1
## Core Structure
frontend/ (Vite+React+TS+ xterm):
- src/App.tsx: Main UI with sidebar (model select, mode, guardrail toggle), prompt buttons (Ollama-style: 'Analyze Code', 'Edit File', 'Run Terminal Cmd', 'Git Commit', 'Full Task'), terminal emulator, live file edit preview, diff viewer.
- src/App.css: Styling for modern Claude-like interface.
- Dependencies: react, xterm, lucide-react for icons, fetch to backend.

tmp_amni_ai/:
- code_knowledge_builder.py: Reused from Amni-Ai for code indexing.
- tools.py: Agent tools for file ops, terminal, git.

backups/: Versioned .bak files.
checklist_full_computer_use_grok_agent.md: Task checklist.
GUARDIAN_COUNCIL_grok_agent.md: Guardian proposals.

## Launcher Integration
- Added to launcher/server.py P list with id "amni-code", launches: dev server (:5180 svc), build (svc).
- Icon: SVG with "C" for code.
- Color: #FF7675.
- Easy launch via launcher/launch.bat → Mission Control UI.

## Dependencies & Relationships
- Reuses Amni-Ai/server.py patterns for /api/computer-use endpoint (tools: read/edit_file, exec_terminal with guard, git_exec).
- Backend: Extend or new server in root for Grok API tool calling (xai grok-beta with tools).
- Guardrails: Toggleable confirm dialog for high-risk cmds (rm, sudo, git push to remote, ssh).
- Agentic: Tool calling loop with planning, execution, verification like code_agent.py but extended for full system.
- Model select: Grok-3, local via ollama, Amni models.
- No func dup: Extend existing handleExecuteAgents to support computer use mode.
- Concise code: No comments, ternary ops, single import block, no empty lines.
- GPU/Async: Use async fetch, parallel tool calls where possible.
- Integration: Live edits update VSCode via vscode api? or file watch.

Relationships: frontend -> localhost:8001/api/grok-agent (new port to avoid conflict with Amni-Ai 8000).
